Defendant Colin ONeill in court with attorney Amber K. Rumpf.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Amended Information filed by the State.  Defense waives the reading.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 & 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  The defense requests the ability to expunge if the defendant successfully completes probation.  State objects to the possibility of expungement.  

Court orders the following: 
Count 1  
- 60 day Jail straight time consecutive to Count 2; STAYED for 1 year Probation concurrent to Count 2.
- Total of $804.25 (fine of $250.00 plus court costs) to be paid as a condition of Probation; alternate 17 days jail;  consecutive
- $350.00 of buy money to be paid to the Metro Drug Unit.

Count 2
- 60 day Jail straight time consecutive to Count 1; STAYED for 1 year Probation concurrent to Count 1.
- Court costs of $243.00 to be paid as a condition of Probation; alternate 4 days jail;  consecutive

- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety.  Submit to an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent.   DNA Sample if not yet provided, surcharge is waived.
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 18, 2014 at 08:30 am.
